  "claim_short": "The packet gives a complete proof of the strict-convex c0 half-space example stated without proof immediately after Conjecture 2.5. With \\[ N(x)^2=\\|x\\|_\\infty^2+\\sum_{n\\ge 1}2^{-n}|x_n|^2 \\] and a positive f=(f_n)\\in \\ell_1 satisfying f_n/2^{-n} unbounded, the open half-space \\[ \\Omega=\\{x\\in c_0:\\sum f_nx_n>0\\} \\] is not geodesic in the quasihyperbolic metric induced by N; in fact no two distinct points of \\Omega...",
